<section id="item-6" class="guide-section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Installation</h2>
  <ul class="bullet-list">
    <li>Download the language and map you want to use.</li>
    <li>You will need a program capable of extracting <b>.7z</b> files.</li>
    <li>
      Locate the game's Workshop folder. For example:
      <b>C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\workshop\content\311210</b>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Inside that folder, find the ID for the map you downloaded. For example:
      <b>3373649394</b> (Mob of the Dead), <b>3558354570</b> (Nuketown Zombies), <b>3435762796</b> (Die Rise).
    </li>
    <li>
      Copy the contents of the downloaded language pack into the map's
      <span class="path">snd\all</span> folder and replace the files.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <img src="/assets/img/Custom/all_folder.png" alt="Map snd/all folder" width="701" height="259" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
</section>

